Uses of Package
fr.cryptohash

  • Packages that use fr.cryptohash 
    Package Description
    fr.cryptohash
    The fr.cryptohash package contains implementations of various cryptographic hash functions.
    fr.cryptohash.test
    The fr.cryptohash.test package contains some test code which can be used to verify that the hash function implementations run correctly, and to measure their speed.
    nxt.util  
  • Classes in fr.cryptohash used by fr.cryptohash 
    Class and Description
    BLAKEBigCore
    This class implements BLAKE-384 and BLAKE-512, which differ only by the IV, output length, and one bit in the padding.
    BLAKESmallCore
    This class implements BLAKE-224 and BLAKE-256, which differ only by the IV, output length, and one bit in the padding.
    BMWBigCore
    This class implements BMW-384 and BMW-512.
    BMWSmallCore
    This class implements BMW-224 and BMW-256.
    CubeHashCore
    This class implements the core operations for the CubeHash digest algorithm.
    Digest
    This interface documents the API for a hash function.
    DigestEngine
    This class is a template which can be used to implement hash functions.
    ECHOBigCore
    This class implements ECHO-384 and ECHO-512.
    ECHOSmallCore
    This class implements ECHO-224 and ECHO-256.
    Fugue2Core
    This class is the base class for Fugue-224 and Fugue-256.
    FugueCore
    This class is the base class for Fugue implementation.
    GroestlBigCore
    This class implements Groestl-384 and Groestl-512.
    GroestlSmallCore
    This class implements Groestl-224 and Groestl-256.
    HamsiBigCore
    This class implements Hamsi-384 and Hamsi-512.
    HamsiSmallCore
    This class implements Hamsi-224 and Hamsi-256.
    HAVALCore
    This class implements the HAVAL digest algorithm, which accepts 15 variants based on the number of passes and digest output.
    JHCore
    This class implements the core operations for the JH digest algorithm.
    KeccakCore
    This class implements the core operations for the Keccak digest algorithm.
    Luffa384
    This class implements Luffa-384 digest algorithm under the Digest API.
    Luffa512
    This class implements Luffa-512 digest algorithm under the Digest API.
    LuffaSmallCore
    This class implements Luffa-224 and Luffa-256.
    MDHelper
    This class implements the padding common to MD4, MD5, the SHA family, and RIPEMD-160.
    SHA2BigCore
    This class implements SHA-384 and SHA-512, which differ only by the IV and the output length.
    SHA2Core
    This class implements SHA-224 and SHA-256, which differ only by the IV and the output length.
    ShabalGeneric
    This class implements Shabal for all output sizes from 32 to 512 bits (inclusive, only multiples of 32 are supported).
    SHAviteBigCore
    This class implements SHAvite-384 and SHAvite-512.
    SHAviteSmallCore
    This class implements SHAvite-224 and SHAvite-256.
    SIMDBigCore
    This class implements SIMD-384 and SIMD-512.
    SIMDSmallCore
    This class implements SIMD-224 and SIMD-256.
    SkeinBigCore
    This class implements the Skein core with a 512-bit internal state ("Skein-512" in the Skein specification terminology).
    SkeinSmallCore
    This class implements the Skein core function when used with a 256-bit internal state ("Skein-256" in the Skein specification terminology).
    TigerCore
    This class implements Tiger and Tiger2, which differ only by the padding.
    WhirlpoolCore
    This class implements the core operations for the Whirlpool digest algorithm family.

    This interface documents the API for a hash function.
